frameDefinitions: This scenario describes a series of Events, associated with a single Participant, i.e., the history of the Participant.
The words in this frame describe entities that occur in some temporally-ordered sequence.
A Defender responds to an Assailant's attack on a Victim by directly, and usually violently, countering it.
A recordable sequence of events is associated with a given Topic.
A Speaker addresses an Audience on a particular Topic.
This frame contains words for Individuals as viewed in terms of their participation in artistic performances.
frameExamples: We've been worried about our recent hire's <t><fex name='Events'>history</fex></t> of deceiving employers.
Describe in detail the <t>sequence</t> of steps taken during an emergency.
Samantha stalwartly <t>defended</t> the gateway from the wraiths, crouching low over Stephen's prone form.
And that is where the <t>history</t> of art begins.
McNamara <t>addressed</t> congress on the state of affairs of the Department of Defense.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Participant</fen> is either an active participant in all of the <fen>Events</fen> (e.g., Agent or Patient), or is more peripherally associated with the <fen>Events</fen> (e.g., Location or Topic).
The <fen>Events</fen> which the <fen>Participant</fen> is a part of. This role is used to mark the frame-evoking element.
When the <fen>Events</fen> concerning the <fen>Participant</fen> occured.
This entity occurs in some sequence with <fen>Entity_2</fen>.
This entity occurs in some sequence with respect to <fen>Entity_1</fen>.
<fen>Entities</fen> that occur in some temporal order.
A characterization of the sequence in which the entities occur.
This role is the being or entity that responds forcefully to the <fen>Assailant</fen>'s attack.
The person (or other self-directed entity) that is attempting physical harm to the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The individual or entity that is under attack from the <fen>Assailant</fen> .
This role identifies the time when the Defender takes forceful action against the Assailant.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Defender</fen> defends the <fen>Victim</fen> from the <fen>Assailant</fen>.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the subject about which the history is given.
When the events concerning the <fen>Topic</fen> occured.
The person or persons to whom the <fen>Speaker</fen> delivers their text.
The person who orally delivers a text about a <fen>Topic</fen> to a passive <fen>Audience</fen>.
What the text that the <fen>Speaker</fen> produces is about.
The <fen>Time</fen> describes when the speaking occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> describes the location where the speaking occurs.
The <fen>Person</fen> is the human being.
listRoleExamples: We've been worried about <fex>our recent hire's</fex> history of deceiving employers.
We will focus on events in her recent <fex>history</fex>.
The study consisted of a <fex>chronologically varied</fex> SERIES of grotesque heads.
The role of the Byzantine Empire in <fex>European</fex> history is not understood by all.
He lectured <fex>to the officers of the Scots Guard</fex>  in  1929.
<fex>You</fex> have to sermonize about the good times
He was the Director: he could lecture <fex>on whomever he liked</fex>.
